"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535113","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-07-22","<p>We have had no such discussions with the British Olympic Association. Sports competition regulations are a matter for the governing body.</p><p> </p><p>Home Nation Sports Councils published the attached guidance in 2013 for national governing bodies of sport entitled &quot;Transsexual people and competitive sport”.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-07-22T13:16:38.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535113/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535113/answer","TranssexualPeopleandCompetitiveSportGuidanceforNationalGoverningBodies.pdf","TranssexualPeopleandCompetitiveSportGuidanceforNationalGoverningBodies.pdf","Transsexual People and Competitive Sport","Transsexual People and Competitive Sport","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535113/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-07-11","Sports Competitors: Gender Recognition","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the International Olympic Committee's (IOC) decision to allow transgender athletes to compete at the Olympic Games; what consultation they have had with the British Olympic Association about that issue; what rules apply in the UK regarding transgender athletes competing in sport; and whether they consider the IOC's ruling to be a disadvantage to non-transgender female athletes.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL1109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535114","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-25","<p>The EU remains united in its strategy of resolving the Ukraine crisis through diplomacy underpinned by robust sanctions pressure. The UK fully supports this policy and will continue to play a central role in calling for a firm response to Russia’s aggression in Ukraine. On 1 July the EU unanimously agreed to renew economic sanctions on Russia for a further six months, in line with the March European Council’s commitment that the duration of sanctions should be clearly linked to the full implementation of the Minsk agreements.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-25T15:47:47.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535114/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535114/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535114/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Russia: Sanctions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action, if any, they plan to take in the light of the resolution of the House of Representatives of the Republic of Cyprus on 7 July calling for an end to the trade and economic sanctions imposed on Russia by the EU, and what their current policy is regarding those sanctions.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL1110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535115","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-27","<p>While we have not made representations to the Government of Israel on this specific issue, we have an ongoing dialogue with the Israeli authorities in order to understand their rules of engagement and express our concerns where necessary.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-27T13:42:47.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535115/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535115/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535115/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel about reports of new rules of engagement for Israeli police allowing the use of live ammunition in response to stone throwing.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535116","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-27","<p>Whilst we have not raised this specific issue with the Government of Israel, officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv have expressed our concern previously over the Israel Defence Forces' use of live fire against fishermen and also about the confiscation of their boats.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-27T13:31:42.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535116/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535116/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535116/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding reports of the confiscation and sinking of fishing boats by Israeli forces in the past three months.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535117","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-19","<p>While we have not made any representations to the Israeli authorities on this specific case, we have raised our concerns with the Israeli authorities in the past about the Israel Defence Forces' use of live fire, urging robust and transparent investigations where appropriate.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-19T15:43:35.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535117/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535117/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535117/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel concerning reports of Israeli troops shooting a Palestinian with Down’s Syndrome who posed no threat to those troops.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535118","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-19","<p>The British Government believes that a negotiated two-state solution is in the interests of both Israel and the Palestinians. While we do not plan to make specific representations to the Government of Israel about the remarks by the UN Secretary General, we will continue to work with our international partners, including the UN, in support of a two-state solution.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-19T15:46:04.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535118/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535118/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535118/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they plan to make to the government of Israel in the light of remarks by the UN Secretary General following his visit to Israel on 28 June urging the Israeli Prime Minister to work towards a negotiated two-state solution.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535119","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-08-02","<p>The British Embassy in Tel Aviv regularly raises the need for equal treatment of all of Israel’s citizens with the Israeli government. Although we have not raised this particular issue, we recognise the importance of equality regarding teacher training, access to education and the role of education in building understanding between communities.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-08-02T13:18:41.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535119/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535119/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Israel: Teachers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel about reports of its intention to reduce the budget for Arab teacher training colleges in Northern Israel to half that of the budget allocated to Jewish teacher training colleges.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535120","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-19","<p>We have serious concerns about the use of punitive demolitions by the Israeli authorities to destroy the homes of the families of Palestinian suspected terrorists. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv have expressed concerns about this policy to a number of Israeli officials: we fear that rather than acting as a deterrent, it has the potential to increase tension. We believe that a stable, well functioning, and fiscally viable Palestinian Authority (PA) is an important contributor to stability, and that it is in Israel’s own interests to secure this stability. As part of this, it is important Israel carries out the regular monthly transfer of tax revenues it collects on behalf of the PA in line with its international obligations.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-19T15:44:45.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535120/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535120/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel concerning reports of continuing and increasing collective punishment of Palestinian communities, including punitive demolitions of private homes in the West Bank and the withholding of tax revenues from the Palestinian Authority.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL1116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535121","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-27","The Government has a range of material, including images, that provides evidence that Daesh has used small, commercially available unmanned aerial vehicles in Syria and Iraq to extend their surveillance capability, produce propaganda material and carry small improvised explosive devices.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-07-27T13:41:25.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535121/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535121/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Islamic State","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what hard evidence they have collected that Daesh is using small commercial drones for surveillance and for conveying explosives.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535122","Home Office","false","2016-07-25","<p>Each of the Government departments and agencies represented at the National Maritime Information Centre has a specific remit and depending on what the nature of the operational scenario in question is, the department or agency with the legislatively proscribed lead responsibility for investigating activity of that kind will take the necessary action. Other departments and agencies will provide support to the lead department or agency as required.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-07-25T10:54:11.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535122/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535122/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-11","Territorial Waters: Security","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 14 June (HL325), how government departments and agencies decide who should take executive action to prosecute a series of contacts of interest.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL1118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535123","Department for Education","false","2016-07-25","<p>The Department for Education does not collect information on the number of children aged 16 or 17 who have presented to their local authority as homeless, or how many have been accommodated as a result of homelessness.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-07-25T12:29:20.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535123/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535123/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Children: Homelessness","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many children aged 16 or 17 have presented to their local authority as homeless, and how many of those were accommodated under the Children Act 1989, in (1) 2015–16, and (2) 2014–15.","false","Biography information for Lord Adebowale",,"Lord Adebowale","HL1119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535124","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-25","<p>One person without a home is one too many. That is why we have maintained and protected homelessness prevention funding for local authorities through the local government finance settlement totalling £315 million by 2019/20. We have also increased central government funding to tackle homelessness to £139 million over the next four years.</p><p>The causes of youth homelessness are highly complex and our priority is to ensure that young people at risk of homelessness get the support they need. That is why we have also invested in the development of a Positive Pathway framework to help local authorities and their partners support young people to remain in the family home (where it is safe to do so) through a collaborative and integrated approach, as well as identifying the relevant support services needed should they become homeless. This includes supported accommodation as a starting point for 16 and 17 year olds.</p><p>Since 2002, 16 to 17 year olds have been classed as a priority need category and are owned a main homeless duty by their local authority. The number of 16 or 17 year olds who applied and were accepted as homeless was 580 in 2014-15, and 530 in 2015-16 (falling from 2,190 in 2009-10). All of these cases were dealt with under the homelessness provisions of Part 7 of the Housing Act 1996.</p><p>We do not hold details on the age of applicants who reported to their local authority but were ineligible or not homeless.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-07-25T15:52:36.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535124/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535124/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535124/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","Homelessness: Children","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many children aged 16 or 17 have presented to their local authority as homeless in (1) 2015–16, and (2) 2014–15, and how many of those were (a) assessed under the Housing Act 1996, and (b) assessed and then accommodated under Part VII of the Housing Act 1996.","false","Biography information for Lord Adebowale",,"Lord Adebowale","HL1120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535125","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-07-22","<p>Ministers expect to receive the report from the Premier League on progress by their clubs to implement the Accessible Stadia guidelines shortly. Ministers meet the football authorities regularly to discuss a variety of matters, including accessibility.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-07-22T13:17:02.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535125/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535125/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535125/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-07-11","Football: Sportsgrounds","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have yet received a report from the Premier League on progress towards the implementation of accessible stadia guidelines by August 2017.","true","Biography information for Lord Faulkner of Worcester",,"Lord Faulkner of Worcester","HL1121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535126","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-07-22","<p>Both the Minister for Disabled People and the Minister for Sport have had discussions and corresponded with both the Premier League and the Football League about improving accessibility at football stadia. The Minister for Sport is meeting the Premier League soon to discuss a range of topics including accessibility and progress with their work plan.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-07-22T13:17:29.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535126/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535126/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535126/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-07-11","Football: Sportsgrounds","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the Premier League and the Football League about meeting disabled access guidelines at football grounds.","true","Biography information for Lord Faulkner of Worcester",,"Lord Faulkner of Worcester","HL1122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535127","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-07-22","<p>Ministerial meetings have taken place with the Rugby Football Union and at official level with the Rugby Union Premier League on accessibility. Ministers are aware that there is both good and bad practice on stadium accessibility across a range of other sports. Ministers expect all sports, and all clubs, whose grounds do not make the reasonable adjustments to accommodate disabled spectators as set out in the Equality Act 2010 to take action to fulfil this legal obligation.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-07-22T13:17:52.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535127/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535127/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535127/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-07-11","Sportsgrounds","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the governing bodies of sports other than football about meeting disabled access guidelines at sports stadia.","true","Biography information for Lord Faulkner of Worcester",,"Lord Faulkner of Worcester","HL1123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535128","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-07-22","<p>As set out in our Sports Strategy, we will enable the Sports Grounds Safety Authority to take on a more formal role in helping sports grounds reach the required standards for accessibility. We are currently in discussions with the SGSA on what role they will play in delivering accessible sports grounds.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-07-22T13:18:05.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535128/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535128/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535128/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-07-11","Sportsgrounds","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have for revising the terms of reference for the Sports Grounds Safety Authority to ensure that they encompass disabled access requirements at licensed sports stadia.","true","Biography information for Lord Faulkner of Worcester",,"Lord Faulkner of Worcester","HL1124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535129","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-25","<p>Members of the public and MPs have requested that this application is called in, and we are currently considering that request.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-07-25T15:48:52.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535129/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535129/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535129/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","Opencast Mining: Northumberland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to call in the decision by Northumberland County Council to approve plans for an opencast coal mine at Highthorn in the light of recent government commitments to phase out the use of coal.","false","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone",,"Baroness Featherstone","HL1125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535130","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-07-25","<p>While the UK remains a member of the EU the existing rules apply and new legislation that applies to the UK will be implemented.</p><p> </p><p>It will be for the new Prime Minister to decide on our future relationship with the EU, including on matters of energy.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-07-25T13:13:52.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535130/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535130/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535130/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Natural Gas","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether in negotiating the UK’s exit from the EU they plan to seek for the UK to be included in any EU regulations on the security of gas supply in times of crisis, as set out in the European Commission’s Proposal for a Regulation concerning measures to safeguard the security of gas supply and repealing Regulation (EU) No 994/2010.","false","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone",,"Baroness Featherstone","HL1126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535131","Department of Health","false","2016-07-20","<p>The arrangements for Genomics England to access patient data are different from the routine data supplied by the Office of National Statistics or other centralised patient data services. The wider patient dataset (including mortality data) will be imported and linked when the genome data is made available to researchers.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-07-20T16:38:40.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535131/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535131/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535131/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-11","Cancer: Screening","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to Written Answer by Lord Prior of Brampton on 7 July (HL829), why Genomic England cannot supply data without delay on the number of patients in the cancer programme who have subsequently died, in the light of the fact that the Office of National Statistics states that the information is available within two months of death from the cancer registry.","false","Biography information for Lord Freyberg",,"Lord Freyberg","HL1127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535132","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-07-19","<p>Regimental museums are provided and sustained by individual Regiments. However, I understand that the Royal Artillery intends to follow the precedent set by the National Army Museum, which is to close all access to the archives and collections during the transition of the Royal Artillery Museum to a new location. I understand that the Royal Artillery is examining ways to provide some access to a limited selection of archive materials whilst it develops longer term plans.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-07-19T16:19:49.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535132/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535132/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535132/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-11","Royal Artillery Museum","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they plan to take to ensure continued public access to the archives and collections of the Royal Artillery museum once the existing site at Woolwich is closed.","false","Biography information for Lord Hutton of Furness",,"Lord Hutton of Furness","HL1128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535133","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-26","<p>On 5 July, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), issued a statement expressing deep concerns about the announcement of new Israeli settlement units in the West Bank, including East Jerusalem. A Foreign and Commonwealth Office spokesperson statement, on 22 June, also expressed concern about Israel’s decision to provide an additional £12 million of funding for settlements. The position of the UK on Israeli settlements is clear: they are illegal under international law, an obstacle to peace and make a two-state solution, with Jerusalem as a shared capital, harder to achieve. We will continue to raise our objections to settlements with the Israeli government.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL1130","2016-07-26T15:28:37.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535133/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535133/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535133/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Occupied Territories: Housing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the most recent Quartet Report's statement that Israel's "continuing policy of settlement and construction" was "steadily eroding the viability of the two-state solution", what specific actions they plan to take in response to the recent decisions by the government of Israel to approve new settlements and to provide a further $18 million to support settlements.","false","Biography information for Lord Judd",,"Lord Judd","HL1129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535134","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-07-26","<p>On 5 July, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), issued a statement expressing deep concerns about the announcement of new Israeli settlement units in the West Bank, including East Jerusalem. A Foreign and Commonwealth Office spokesperson statement, on 22 June, also expressed concern about Israel’s decision to provide an additional £12 million of funding for settlements. The position of the UK on Israeli settlements is clear: they are illegal under international law, an obstacle to peace and make a two-state solution, with Jerusalem as a shared capital, harder to achieve. We will continue to raise our objections to settlements with the Israeli government.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL1129","2016-07-26T15:28:37.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535134/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535134/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535134/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Occupied Territories","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what specific action they are taking in response to the number of Israeli settlers in occupied Palestinian territories.","false","Biography information for Lord Judd",,"Lord Judd","HL1130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535135","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-21","<p>The Government made its position clear in our ‘Guidance to Local Councils on Good Practice in the Collection of Council Tax Arrears’, June 2013. This highlights the importance of councils being sympathetic to those in genuine hardship and that they are proportionate in their enforcement action, as well as noting the support that should be provided to vulnerable people.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-07-21T13:41:01.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535135/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535135/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535135/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","Council Tax: Arrears","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the Citizens Advice Bureau report <i>Catching Up: improving council tax arrears collection</i> published on 8 July, and of why that report does not refer to the guidance to local councils on good practice in the collection of council tax arrears in respect of vulnerable people published by the Department for Communities and Local Government in June 2013.","false","Biography information for Lord Ramsbotham",,"Lord Ramsbotham","HL1131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535136","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-08-03","<p>The Government has no such plans.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL1135","2016-08-03T14:43:24.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535136/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535136/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535136/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to invoke Article 50 of the TEU immediately; and whether they will negotiate to withdraw from the EU within months, and not later than March 2017.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535137","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-08-03","<p>Officials at the UK Permanent Representation act on the basis of Ministerial instructions, which will continue to be the case in the run up to and throughout the period of negotiations to exit the EU. The UK remains a full member of the EU until our leave withdrawal is completed. Consequently, rights and obligations in the EU Treaties and other EU law continue to apply until that time.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-08-03T14:43:55.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535137/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535137/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535137/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what instructions they have given to ensure that UK representatives in the EU Committee of Permanent Representatives (1) do not commit the UK to any new policies prior to withdrawal from the EU, and (2) facilitate a swift and effective withdrawal from the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535138","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-20","<p>A new Department for Exiting the European Union has been established by the Prime Minister. The Department will lead the UK’s negotiations to leave the European Union and establish the future relationship between the EU and the UK, working closely with the UK’s devolved administrations, Parliament, and a wide range of other interested parties on this approach. Officials and ministers will work closely with other departments, including the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, the Department for International Trade and others, to ensure the British public and business interests get the best possible deal when the UK leave the EU.</p>",,"Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen",,"2016-07-20T16:42:15.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535138/answer","Biography information for Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535138/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535138/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what instructions they have given to all ministers of the Crown and senior civil servants to work to facilitate an early and effective withdrawal from the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535139","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-08-03","<p>The Government has no such plans.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL1132","2016-08-03T14:43:24.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535139/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535139/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to accelerate negotiations to leave the EU to ensure that they are completed before July 2017 when the UK is due to take over the Presidency of the Council of the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535140","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-25","<p>I can confirm that as part of the public inquiry into the Leeds New Generation Transport Scheme the Inspector did not visit any European city operating trolley bus systems to see if its system could be emulated in Leeds. The Inspector had regard to all the evidence put to the inquiry, this may have included information about other trolley bus schemes in the world, however the Inspector's remit was to look at the scheme for Leeds specifically put forward by the Applicant, having regard to the evidence submitted by all parties to the case.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-07-25T15:49:23.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535140/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535140/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535140/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","Trolleybuses: Leeds","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the planning inspector of the public inquiry into the Leeds New Generation Transport schemes visited any European city operating trolley bus systems to ascertain whether its system could be emulated in Leeds, and if not, why not.","true","Biography information for Lord Stoddart of Swindon",,"Lord Stoddart of Swindon","HL1136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535141","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-20","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>",,"Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen",,"2016-07-20T16:37:52.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535141/answer","Biography information for Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535141/answer","UKSA Response to HL1137 (1) (1) (1).pdf","UKSA Response to HL1137 (1) (1) (1).pdf","UKSA Response to HL1137 ","UKSA Response to HL1137 ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535141/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Overseas Students: Statistics","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress the Office of National Statistics has made in understanding non-EU student arrivals and departures in order to track the progress of student cohorts through the immigration system, as outlined in its January 2016 report <i>Population Briefing, International Student Migration</i><i>- what do the statistics tell</i><i>us?</i>","false","Biography information for Lord Green of Deddington",,"Lord Green of Deddington","HL1137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535142","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-14","<p>The Committee on Toxicity of Chemicals in Food, Consumer Products and the Environment (COT) identified and evaluated over 400 references when producing their 2007 statement, called “Statement on the Review of the Cabin Air Environment, Ill-health in Aircraft Crews and the Possible Relationship to Smoke/Fume Events in Aircraft”. The evidence base consisted of data submitted by the British Airline Pilots Association (BALPA) and references identified as relevant by the COT Secretariat.</p><p> </p><p>All evidence reviewed can be found listed at the end of the Statement. There are no references to ExxonMobil submitting evidence, or being consulted by the COT during the review.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-07-14T10:58:34.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535142/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535142/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535142/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-11","Aircraft: Air Conditioning","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 11 July (HL873), whether ExxonMobil was consulted by, or supplied evidence to, the Committee on Toxicity of Chemicals in Food and the Environment (COT) prior to the publication of the 2007 COT Statement and whether the results were conclusive.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL1138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535143","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-13","<p>Members of the public can report excessively smoky lorries and buses to the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency through their website (https://www.gov.uk/report-smoky-vehicle). There is no similar reporting system for cars or other vehicles. However all vehicles must meet strict standards before they enter service, as well as standards which must be maintained at all times while a vehicle is in service. It is the owner’s responsibility to ensure that the vehicle meets the necessary limit requirements at all times.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2016-07-13T14:45:17.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535143/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535143/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-07-11","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether it is possible for members of the public who encounter a motor vehicle producing visible emissions to report the matter and if so, to whom should they report.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL1139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535144","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-07-25","<p>The Greening Government Commitments annual report for 2014-15 sets out the data reported by departments on the proportion of government procurement contracts in a number of key product groups which met or exceeded Government Buying Standards in that year. The information specifically on construction contracts is set out in Annex 2, procurement table 3 of the annual report. As with previous years’ annual reports, the available data is presented by department, rather than for the whole of government. It is not possible to provide a figure on the proportion which met or exceeded the Government Buying Standards for the whole of government, as not all departments were able to report complete information.</p><p>It is the responsibility of each Department to put the Government Buying Standards into practice in its own procurement activity.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-07-25T15:58:45.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535144/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535144/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-07-11","Government Departments: Procurement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage, by total value, of government departments’ procurement contracts for relevant construction projects meet or exceed the mandatory Government Buying Standard level in 2014–15; and why that data was not included in the Greening Government Commitments annual report for 2014–15.","false","Biography information for Baroness Parminter",,"Baroness Parminter","HL1140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535145","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-08-03","<p>There are sizeable Russian-speaking communities in Latvia and Estonia, and a smaller community in Lithuania. All EU Member States are obliged to meet the standards for minority rights and are subject to obligations and monitoring mechanisms, such as through the Council of Europe. Our Embassies in the Baltic States have supported programmes run by their host governments and non-governmental organisations to encourage integration, tolerance, diversity and respect for minorities - including programmes to support media plurality and social cohesion.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-08-03T14:44:49.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535145/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535145/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-07-11","Baltic States: Russia","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of (1) the treatment of Russian minorities in the Baltic States, particularly Lithuania, and (2) whether such treatment would attract a response from Russia; and if so, what type of response that would be.","false","Biography information for Lord Pearson of Rannoch",,"Lord Pearson of Rannoch","HL1141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535146","Department of Health","false","2016-07-14","<p>The Tobacco Control Plan is currently being developed and Ministers will decide on an appropriate publication date in due course.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-07-14T14:57:10.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535146/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535146/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-07-11","Tobacco","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government on what date they plan to publish the Tobacco Control Plan for England.","false","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham",,"Lord Young of Cookham","HL1142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535148","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-07-25","<p>The Government will continue taking forward the important legislation that was set before Parliament in the Queen’s Speech, including the Higher Education and Research Bill. This includes the formation of the new body UK Research and Innovation (UKRI). Now, more than ever, we need a strong and unified voice to represent the interests of UK research and innovation across Europe and around the world which UKRI will provide.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","42297","2016-07-25T14:31:33.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535148/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535148/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Research Councils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will postpone the reorganisation of UK Science Research Councils until the UK has renegotiated its relationship with the EU.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","42296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535149","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-07-25","<p>The Government will continue taking forward the important legislation that was set before Parliament in the Queen’s Speech, including the Higher Education and Research Bill. This includes the formation of the new body UK Research and Innovation (UKRI). Now, more than ever, we need a strong and unified voice to represent the interests of UK research and innovation across Europe and around the world which UKRI will provide.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","42296","2016-07-25T14:31:33.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535149/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535149/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Research Councils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of UK negotiations with the EU resulting from the outcome of the referendum on the planned reorganisation of UK Science Research Councils proposed by Sir Paul Nurse.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","42297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535150","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-07-20","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The UK’s decision to leave the EU has no immediate effect on the right of researchers to apply or to participate in Horizon 2020 as the UK is still an EU member state. UK participants can continue to apply to the programme in the usual way. The Commission has made a public statement on its website to this effect. The future of UK access to European research and innovation funding will be determined as part of wider discussions with the EU.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-20T15:21:16.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535150/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535150/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Science: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he plans to take to protect UK science from the effect of uncertainty about access to European Research Council grants.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","42298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535151","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-07-21","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The UK has a long established system that supports, and therefore attracts, the brightest minds, at all stages of their careers. We fund excellent research wherever it is found, and ensure there is the freedom to tackle important scientific questions. The Government is committed to maintaining and enhancing the strength of our research base, which is why at the Spending Review we committed to protect the science budget in real terms from its 2015/16 level of £4.7 billion per annum.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has said that there will be no immediate changes in circumstances for EU citizens working or studying in the UK - this includes scientists and engineers.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-21T16:04:56.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535151/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535151/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Engineering and Science","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the outcome of the referendum on UK membership of the EU, if he will take steps to help the UK retain its leading scientists and engineers.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","42300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535152","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-08-10","<p>My Rt hon Friend the Member for Bromsgrove (Sajid Javid) visited Redcar on 2 October 2015 following the announcement of the liquidation of Sahaviriya Steel Industries UK (SSI).</p><p> </p><p>The then Secretary of State announced a support package worth up to £80 million for former employees affected by the closure. He was accompanied by the then Minister for Small Businesses, Industry and Enterprise, Anna Soubry.</p><p> </p><p>The Minister for Small Businesses, Industry and Enterprise then attended the Redcar taskforce on 21 March 2016.</p><p> </p><p>In his previous role as Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, my Rt hon Friend met the Mayor and Leaders of the five Tees Valley authorities on the following dates: 15 July 2015 (a joint meeting with James Wharton), 23 March 2016, 7 June 2016 (to launch Lord Heseltine’s report <em>Tees Valley: opportunity unlimited</em>) and 12 July 2016. These were regular catch-up meetings, which took place in Westminster.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-08-10T05:59:25.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535152/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535152/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, which official engagements he has undertaken in Redcar since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","42349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535153","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-07-20","<p>The Government recognises the importance of our research base, which is why we have protected the science resource budget in real terms from its 2015/16 level of £4.7 billion for the rest of the parliament.</p><p> </p><p>The future of UK access to European research and innovation funding will be a matter for the new Prime Minister and government to decide. The Government is determined to ensure that the UK continues to play a leading role in European and international research and innovation.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-20T15:19:35.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535153/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535153/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Research: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to safeguard levels of research funding in universities as a result of the outcome of the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","42371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535154","Department for Education","false","2016-07-21","<p>The Government has met a number of stakeholders since the referendum for meetings that included discussion of EU issues. The Government continues to work closely with the higher education sector[1] and to listen to their feedback on the implications of the referendum outcome. The Government will continue to engage with the whole HE sector on these important issues and welcome their valuable input.</p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/statement-on-higher-education-and-research-following-the-eu-referendum" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/statement-on-higher-education-and-research-following-the-eu-referendum</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-21T16:16:49.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535154/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535154/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Universities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what representations she has (a) made to and (b) received from universities on the implications of the outcome of the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","42372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535155","Department for Education","false","2016-07-20","<p>Existing rules on EU and other EEA students remain in force. This means that existing EU and other EEA nationals and their family members eligible to receive student support (including loans) will continue to receive that support until they finish their courses. This applies to those who are either currently studying or who will begin courses in academic year 2016/17.</p><p>Further information is provided in a statement made by the Student Loans Company: <a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/media/latest-news/eu-nationals-and-student-finance-in-england.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/media/latest-news/eu-nationals-and-student-finance-in-england.aspx </a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-20T16:19:04.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535155/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535155/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Overseas Students: EEA Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to safeguard the status of non-UK EEA students in the UK as a result of the outcome of the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","42373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535156","Department for Education","false","2016-08-02","<p>The EU referendum result has no immediate effect on students abroad or those applying for 2016/17. Payments will be made in the usual way. Access after we leave the EU is a matter for the forthcoming negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-08-02T13:46:30.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535156/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535156/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Foreign Students: European Economic Area","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to safeguard the status of UK nationals studying in other member states of the EEA as a result of the outcome of the referendum on the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","42374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535157","Department for Education","false","2016-08-01","<p>There are no immediate changes following the EU Referendum, including in the circumstances of British citizens studying, or planning to study, in the EU. Future arrangements for studying abroad will need to be considered as part of wider discussions about the UK’s relationship with the EU.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-08-01T13:10:29.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535157/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535157/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Foreign Students: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to reassure university students that the outcome of the EU referendum will not prevent those students from studying abroad in Europe.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","42397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535158","Department for Education","false","2016-07-19","<p>The law determining eligibility for student finance is unchanged. EU nationals who have resided in the EEA for at least three years are granted “home” fee status for the duration of their courses. This is the case for all eligible EU nationals currently studying in English universities, and for those beginning courses in the 2016/17 Academic year.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-07-19T15:38:10.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535158/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535158/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Overseas Students: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to reassure European students studying abroad in Britain that the outcome of the EU referendum will not lead to changes to the tuition fee arrangements of those students.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","42398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535159","Department for Education","false","2016-07-28","<p>To ensure that apprenticeships are focused on providing sustained and substantial training, they must last for at least 12 months. We do not set a maximum duration centrally, but apprenticeships generally take between one and four years to complete.</p><p>The suggested duration of each apprenticeship is set by employers when designing the apprenticeship standard.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-07-28T15:05:20.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535159/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535159/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the maximum duration is of an apprenticeship.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","42436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535160","Department for Education","false","2016-07-29","<p>Some market and economic volatility can be expected as the process for leaving the EU unfolds. In recent years, however, the UK has been the fastest growing economy in the G7 and one of the strongest major advanced economies in the world. The Government has already outlined how this strength means that we are as well-placed as any economy could be to meet any economic challenges that lie ahead.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-07-29T13:16:58.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535160/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535160/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the implications of market uncertainty following the EU referendum for progress in meeting her target for creating new apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","42434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535161","Department for Education","false","2016-07-29","<p>Degree Apprenticeships are designed by groups of employers working with higher education institutions and will be driven by employer demand.</p><p>We therefore do not use a top-down estimate of how many Degree Apprenticeships will be taken up by 2020, as part of our overall commitment to 3 million starts.</p><p>Degree Apprenticeships provide a valuable route for people to obtain a degree-level qualification alongside training for a career, with employment from day one.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2016-07-29T13:17:22.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535161/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535161/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-11","Apprentices: Degrees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of how many degree apprenticeship places will be taken up by 2020.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","42435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535162","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-09-13","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The new Department for Exiting the European Union will be made up of staff from various departments across Government. The overall size and scope of the new department, including staffing and budget, are under consideration.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-09-13T15:18:59.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535162/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535162/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-07-11","Cabinet Office EU Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many full-time equivalent staff of his Department (a) have moved and (b) are planned to move into the EU Unit.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","42453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535163","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-07-14","<p>There a number of departments across Whitehall who work on aspects of the Digital Single Market (DSM) including the Department for Culture Media and Sport, the Home Office and HM Treasury. And, within the Department for Business Innovation and Skills (BIS) there are a number of policy areas that are involved directly or indirectly in aspects of the Digital Single Market including the Intellectual Property Office, Competition and Consumer Policy and Advanced Manufacturing and Services.</p><p> </p><p>BIS leads on behalf of Government and coordinates activity across those departments with an interest. There is a core team of five FTEs who act as the hub for all of this work.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-07-14T13:07:53.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535163/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535163/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-07-11","Digital Technology: EU Internal Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many full-time equivalent staff of his Department are working on the Digital Single Market.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","42455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535164","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-18","<p>A new Department for Exiting the European Union has been established by the Prime Minister. The staffing requirements for the new department are now being identified. <strong></strong></p><p> </p>","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis",,"2016-07-18T10:48:45.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535164/answer","Biography information for Mr David Davis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535164/answer","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535164/answer/previousversion/7205",,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Cabinet Office EU Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans the EU Unit has to recruit staff (a) from within and (b) externally to the Civil Service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","42456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535165","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-14","<p>The number of Cabinet Office non payroll staff (excluding contractors) as of May 2016, is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/payroll-costs-and-non-consolidated-pay-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/payroll-costs-and-non-consolidated-pay-data</a></p><p> </p><p>The overall total spend on agency and temporary staff in FY 2015/16 is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cabinet-office-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cabinet-office-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</a></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-07-14T07:54:57.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535165/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535165/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Cabinet Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many contract staff are employed in his Department; and what the total wage bill (a) is in 2016-17 and (b) was in 2015-16 for such staff.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","42457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535166","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-18","<p>The government does not comment on ongoing litigation.</p>","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","42416","2016-07-18T10:50:29.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535166/answer","Biography information for Mr David Davis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535166/answer","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535166/answer/previousversion/7204",,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate the Government has made of the legal costs it will incur in connection with the legal case brought by Mishcon de Reya in respect of Article 50 of the Treaty of European Union.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","42415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535167","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-18","<p>The government does not comment on ongoing litigation.</p>","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","42415","2016-07-18T10:50:29.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535167/answer","Biography information for Mr David Davis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535167/answer","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535167/answer/previousversion/7206",,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the Government's legal costs have been to date  in connection with the legal case brought by Mishcon de Reya in respect of Article 50 of the Treaty of European Union.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","42416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535168","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-18","<p>The Prime Minister will take the decision about when to trigger article 50 and start the formal process of leaving the EU. She has been clear that the will of the British people must be respected and delivered.</p>","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis",,"2016-07-18T10:49:32.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535168/answer","Biography information for Mr David Davis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535168/answer","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535168/answer/previousversion/7207",,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether once Article 50 of the Treaty of the European Union has been triggered it can be untriggered before the UK's negotiations on withdrawal from the EU have been completed.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","42388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535169","Home Office","false","2016-07-13","<p>The previous Government signed the Istanbul Convention to show the strong commitment it placed on tackling violence against women and girls and this Government remains committed to ratifying it.</p><p>The UK already complies with the vast majority of the Convention’s articles but further amendments to domestic law, to take extra-territorial jurisdiction over a range of offences (as required by Article 44), are necessary before the Convention can be ratified.</p><p>We are currently considering the approach to implementing the extra-territorial jurisdiction requirements in England and Wales and will seek to legislate when the approach is agreed and Parliamentary time allows.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-07-13T15:19:13.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535169/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535169/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-07-11","Council of Europe Convention on Preventing and Combating Violence against Women and Domestic Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the Government plans to ratify the Istanbul Convention.","false","Biography information for Natalie McGarry","Glasgow East","Natalie McGarry","42317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535170","Cabinet Office","false","2016-07-19","<p>As set out in our manifesto, the Government will bring forward legislation to remove the outdated 15 year time limit on overseas voting rights.</p><p>The Government’s proposals will make no change to the extent to which taxation is the basis for enfranchisement in the UK.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2016-07-19T13:09:26.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535170/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535170/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-07-11","Voting Rights: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to allow all British citizens who live abroad but pay income tax in the UK to vote in UK elections regardless of the length of time they have been resident abroad.","false","Biography information for Gordon Henderson","Sittingbourne and Sheppey","Gordon Henderson","42319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535171","HM Treasury","false","2016-07-14","<p>For 2015-16 HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) dealt with a) 620 income tax post-transaction checks and b) 39 PAYE health checks.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not retain directly accessible data that allows identification of what proportion of each of these checks were made by small and medium enterprises.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-07-14T07:53:59.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535171/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535171/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-07-11","Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Financial Secretary to the Treasury of 27 June 2016, Official Report, column 72, how many (a) income tax post-transaction valuation checks and (b) PAYE health checks were made in 2015-16; and what proportion of each of those checks were made by SMEs.","false","Biography information for Roger Mullin","Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","Roger Mullin","42310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535172","HM Treasury","false","2016-07-14","<p>The transition from the Business Review of the Collection Service, more commonly known as BROCS, to the Real Time Information System did not cause the write off of debt.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-07-14T07:51:43.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535172/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535172/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-07-11","Tax Collection: Debts Written Off","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department made of the value of debts written off during HM Revenue and Customs' switch from the Business Review of the Collection Service to the Real Time Information system.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","42289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535173","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-19","<p>The Government announced in December that it would consider giving more responsibility to councils in England to support older people with care needs – including people who, under the current system, would be supported through Attendance Allowance.</p><p>Any new responsibilities would be matched by the transfer of the equivalent spending power - this is a reform policy, not a savings measure. We are not considering any changes for existing Attendance Allowance claimants and, should devolution proceed, everyone already claiming Attendance Allowance at the point of devolution will continue to receive it.</p><p>The Government is currently consulting on the implementation of commitments on 100% business rates retention for councils in England. The consultation seeks views on options for devolving new responsibilities to local government as part of those reforms, and this is one of the options about which we are consulting. The consultation document is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/self-sufficient-local-government-100-business-rates-retention" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/self-sufficient-local-government-100-business-rates-retention</a></p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-07-19T14:53:38.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535173/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535173/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","Attendance Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what savings his Department expects to accrue to the public purse as a result of transferring attendance allowance funding to councils; and whether those savings will be retained centrally or used for other benefits expenditure.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","42360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535174","Women and Equalities","false","2016-07-14","<p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission is an independent body, but wholly funded by Government. Full information on its budgets since 2010/11 can be found in its Annual Reports at the following links: <a href="https://www.equalityhumanrights.com/en/corporate-reporting/annual-reports" target="_blank">https://www.equalityhumanrights.com/en/corporate-reporting/annual-reports</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-07-14T14:01:51.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535174/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535174/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-07-11","Equality and Human Rights Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what funding her Department has provided to the Equality and Human Rights Commission in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","42433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535175","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-14","<p>The published target date for issuing the decision is on or before 28 September. My Department does of course attempt to reach planning decisions in advance of target dates when this is practical.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-07-14T08:41:56.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535175/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535175/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","London City Airport: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he expects a decision to be taken on London City Airport's planning application.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","42444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535176","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-14","<p>We are still considering responses to the proposed changes to the National Planning Policy Framework, including on the housing delivery test.</p><p>The Government has put in place the strongest protections for the Green Belt. The Framework is clear that inappropriate development will not be allowed unless there are very special circumstances, and that Green Belt boundaries should be adjusted only in exceptional circumstances, through the Local Plan process. The Framework also encourages development of brownfield land, and we have undertaken to ensure that 90 per cent of brownfield land suitable for housing will have planning permissions for new homes in place by the end of this Parliament.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-07-14T08:39:50.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535176/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535176/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-07-11","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that suitable brownfield sites are prioritised for development over greenbelt sites under the proposed Housing Delivery Test.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","42445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535177","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-07-14","<p>Improving mobile coverage remains a priority for the Government, and our landmark agreement in December 2014 with the four mobile network operators (MNOs) for each to provide voice and SMS text coverage to at least 90% of the UK landmass by 2017 will significantly improve coverage in the UK, including the Liverpool City Region. The additional licence obligation on Telefonica, which the other MNOs have publicly stated they will match, will deliver significant improvements in 4G coverage - covering 98% of UK premises by the end of 2017.</p><p> </p><p>In support of this work, the Government is also reforming mobile planning laws (in England only) and the Electronic Communications Code to make it cheaper and quicker for industry to invest and deliver coverage improvements.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-07-14T09:22:12.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535177/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/535177/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-07-11","Mobile Phones: Liverpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he has taken to improve mobile telephone coverage in the Liverpool City Region.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","42417"
